# Crate dialoguerCopy item path

Summary[Source](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/src/dialoguer/lib.rs.html#1-64)
Expand description
dialoguer is a library for Rust that helps you build useful small interactive user inputs for the command line. It provides utilities to render various simple dialogs like confirmation prompts, text inputs and more.
Best paired with other libraries in the family:
  * [indicatif](https://docs.rs/indicatif)
  * [console](https://docs.rs/console)


## [§](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/dialoguer/#crate-contents)Crate Contents
  * Confirmation prompts
  * Input prompts (regular and password)
  * Input validation
  * Selections prompts (single and multi)
  * Fuzzy select prompt
  * Other kind of prompts
  * Editor launching


## [§](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/dialoguer/#crate-features)Crate Features
The following crate features are available:
  * `editor`: enables bindings to launch editor to edit strings
  * `fuzzy-select`: enables fuzzy select prompt
  * `history`: enables input prompts to be able to track history of inputs
  * `password`: enables password input prompt
  * `completion`: enables ability to implement custom tab-completion for input prompts


By default `editor` and `password` are enabled.
## Re-exports[§](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/dialoguer/#reexports)

`pub use console[](https://docs.rs/console/0.15.11/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/console/index.html "mod console");`

## Modules[§](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/dialoguer/#modules)

[theme](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/dialoguer/theme/index.html "mod dialoguer::theme")
    Customizes the rendering of the elements.

Summary[Source](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/src/dialoguer/lib.rs.html#1-64)
Expand description
dialoguer is a library for Rust that helps you build useful small interactive user inputs for the command line. It provides utilities to render various simple dialogs like confirmation prompts, text inputs and more.
Best paired with other libraries in the family:
  * [indicatif](https://docs.rs/indicatif)
  * [console](https://docs.rs/console)


## [§](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/dialoguer/#crate-contents)Crate Contents
  * Confirmation prompts
  * Input prompts (regular and password)
  * Input validation
  * Selections prompts (single and multi)
  * Fuzzy select prompt
  * Other kind of prompts
  * Editor launching


## [§](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/dialoguer/#crate-features)Crate Features
The following crate features are available:
  * `editor`: enables bindings to launch editor to edit strings
  * `fuzzy-select`: enables fuzzy select prompt
  * `history`: enables input prompts to be able to track history of inputs
  * `password`: enables password input prompt
  * `completion`: enables ability to implement custom tab-completion for input prompts


By default `editor` and `password` are enabled.
## Re-exports[§](https://docs.rs/dialoguer/latest/dialoguer/#reexports)

`pub use console[](https://docs.rs/console/0.15.11/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/console/index.html "mod console");`

enriched_crate.readme_summary: The `dialoguer` crate enables interactive command-line user inputs in Rust, offering features like confirmation prompts, text and password inputs, input validation, single/multi-selection, fuzzy search, and editor integration. It supports customizable themes, input history tracking, and tab-completion, with optional features such as password input and editor launching enabled by default. Ideal for building user-friendly CLI applications, it pairs well with related crates like `indicatif` and `console`.
enriched_crate.factual_counterfactual:
### Pair 1: Input Prompts  
✅ **Factual**: The `dialoguer` crate provides support for input prompts, including password inputs, with optional input validation through custom validators.  
❌ **Counterfactual**: The `dialoguer` crate only supports plain text input prompts and does not provide password input functionality or validation mechanisms.  

---

### Pair 2: Fuzzy Select Feature  
✅ **Factual**: The `dialoguer` crate includes a `fuzzy-select` feature, which allows users to search and select items interactively using fuzzy matching.  
❌ **Counterfactual**: The `dialoguer` crate does not support fuzzy matching in selection prompts and requires users to manually scroll through options without search capabilities.  

---

### Pair 3: Editor Integration  
✅ **Factual**: The `dialoguer` crate includes an `editor` feature that enables launching the system's default text editor for editing strings.  
❌ **Counterfactual**: The `dialoguer` crate does not provide any functionality for launching external editors and requires all input to be handled directly in the terminal.
